column1: The  Court  of  Appeal  held  that  it  is  quite  evident  that  the  impugned  Quit  Notice  of
19.10.2011 is the same as Quit Notice of 26.08.2005 impugned in C.A. (Writ) Application
No. 323/2006 which was quashed by the Court of Appeal. Accordingly, Court held that the
impugned Quit Notice of 19.10.2011 is null and void in law as the 1st Respondent had no
authority in law to re-issue a notice to quit. Moreover, it was held that the 1st Respondent
has failed to identify the corpus properly. The Court of Appeal issued a Writ of Certiorari
This appeal has been filed by the 2nd Respondent-Petitioner (“Petitioner”) against the said
judgment of the Court of Appeal. Leave to appeal was granted on the following questions:
